05:03.081 --> 05:04.778
DARKO: You're not gonna open up?

05:06.884 --> 05:09.481
Boss doesn't trust you with the keys?

05:11.053 --> 05:14.822
FALCO: He doesn't trust
anyone with anything.

05:14.891 --> 05:18.093
DARKO: This town is a dump.

05:18.161 --> 05:21.096
FALCO: Maybe
you should've stayed in prison.

05:23.600 --> 05:26.201
FALCO: You know what I don't get?

05:26.269 --> 05:29.502
How'd you ever get a deal?

05:29.572 --> 05:30.838
DARKO: I made a deal, you made a deal.

05:30.906 --> 05:32.106
Same-same.

05:32.175 --> 05:34.074
FALCO: No, it's not the same-same.

05:34.144 --> 05:36.043
I never murdered anyone.

05:36.112 --> 05:38.980
DARKO: It wasn't my finger
that pulled that trigger.

05:39.048 --> 05:41.548
FALCO: Pretty close.

05:41.617 --> 05:44.016
DARKO: Tell me something, Chef.

05:44.086 --> 05:47.954
Anybody ever die doing
that crank you cooked?

05:52.629 --> 05:55.262
DARKO: You're no cleaner than me.

05:58.268 --> 06:00.466
(engine approaching)

06:05.875 --> 06:06.406
(truck door slams)

06:06.406 --> 06:07.807
FALCO: Thought we had till next Friday.

06:07.877 --> 06:09.576
BULLET: You and me both.

06:09.644 --> 06:10.709
FALCO: So how long
is this going to take?

06:10.779 --> 06:11.879
BULLET: Well, you tell me.

06:11.947 --> 06:13.213
It's one of The Devil's tests.

06:13.281 --> 06:15.014
But if we're gonna get
patched into this club

06:15.084 --> 06:16.250
and move our mission down field,

06:16.317 --> 06:18.850
we're gonna have to get
used to passing tests.

06:18.920 --> 06:20.552
Listen, I got some beer
in the back of the truck.

06:20.622 --> 06:21.821
You boys mind grabbing it?

06:21.889 --> 06:23.221
Stash it at the bar.

06:23.292 --> 06:26.057
FALCO: Sure, it's just...
I got this dinner thing.

06:26.127 --> 06:27.927
BULLET: Listen, hopefully
we'll make it outta here

06:27.995 --> 06:28.935
in a couple of hours.

06:28.935 --> 06:30.297
In the meanwhile,
we got an ATF clubhouse

06:30.365 --> 06:33.531
that is wired for sound,
so let's start using it.

06:35.302 --> 06:39.105
(shuffling sounds)

06:39.701 --> 06:42.774
DARKO:
"I've got this dinner I gotta do."

06:42.843 --> 06:45.543
FALCO: Yeah, well,
at least some of us have a life.

06:47.014 --> 06:50.548
♪

06:50.617 --> 06:55.553
♪

06:55.622 --> 07:00.492
♪

07:00.560 --> 07:05.497
♪

07:05.565 --> 07:08.499
♪

07:08.567 --> 07:11.636
♪

07:11.704 --> 07:13.571
BUG: Hey.

07:13.639 --> 07:15.473
What's with all the beer?

07:15.541 --> 07:18.076
DARKO: Only thing worse than
a drunk Outlaw is a sober one.

07:19.980 --> 07:21.112
FALCO: What the hell are you wearing?

07:21.180 --> 07:23.079
BUG: This? It's my new biker jacket.

07:23.149 --> 07:24.180
Why, do you like it?

07:24.250 --> 07:25.783
Could get you one if you want.

07:25.851 --> 07:26.850
FALCO: Just tell me you didn't steal it?

07:26.918 --> 07:28.819
BUG: I didn't steal it.

07:28.887 --> 07:30.153
FALCO: Look,
we got a lot of work to do, man.

07:30.223 --> 07:32.689
Go get the rest of the
beer from the truck.

07:32.759 --> 07:33.891
BUG: What?

07:33.959 --> 07:35.826
You're not wearing that.
Not around real bikers.

07:35.894 --> 07:37.995
BUG: Does the new guy really
get to boss me around?

07:38.064 --> 07:39.028
Because seniority.

07:39.098 --> 07:41.630
DARKO: Stupidity cancels seniority.

07:41.699 --> 07:43.933
He wears this, we all look like mooks.

07:44.002 --> 07:45.769
FALCO: Beer now.

07:49.141 --> 07:51.908
DARKO: That guy? Not helping.

07:51.978 --> 07:53.944
- FALCO: Yeah, he is.
- DARKO: How?

07:54.012 --> 07:55.045
FALCO: By being 'that guy.'

07:55.113 --> 07:56.012
There's one of them in every club.

07:56.081 --> 07:57.646
Makes us look real.

07:58.750 --> 08:01.184
(beer bottles clinking)

08:03.689 --> 08:05.588
BULLET: Hey, Bug, you're late.

08:05.656 --> 08:06.790
We got less than 20 minutes.

08:06.858 --> 08:07.923
Okay, I need you
to grab the tools and crap

08:07.992 --> 08:09.593
and stash them out back.

08:09.661 --> 08:10.860
BUG: Okay.

08:12.629 --> 08:14.863
BULLET: Hey. Everything okay?

08:14.932 --> 08:16.165
(Falco takes inhaler)

08:16.233 --> 08:17.867
FALCO: We'll see.

08:20.237 --> 08:25.141
♪

08:25.209 --> 08:30.077
♪

08:30.146 --> 08:35.082
♪

08:35.152 --> 08:37.653
♪

08:37.721 --> 08:38.620
(sledgehammer slams on table)

08:39.789 --> 08:41.590
FALCO: Come on.

08:41.658 --> 08:42.409
DARKO: What?

08:42.409 --> 08:43.527
FALCO: I put a lot of work into this.

08:43.527 --> 08:45.759
DARKO: Oh, you did? Is that right?

08:45.828 --> 08:49.864
(sledgehammer slamming on table)

08:49.933 --> 08:53.634
DARKO: It's a clubhouse.
It's not a nightclub.

08:53.702 --> 08:55.702
Stash it behind the bar.

08:55.772 --> 08:56.938
BULLET: Alright.

08:57.006 --> 08:58.572
Come on.

08:58.642 --> 09:02.043
♪

09:02.110 --> 09:04.446
BULLET: The Devil and his
boys are not coming here to

09:04.514 --> 09:06.179
admire the decor.

09:06.249 --> 09:08.950
They're gonna test us,
especially you new boys.

09:09.018 --> 09:12.986
So keep your stories straight,
go easy on the beers,

09:13.056 --> 09:15.623
and remember that everything
is being recorded for evidence.

09:15.692 --> 09:19.525
That said,
don't go asking leading questions.

09:19.595 --> 09:22.096
They're paranoid enough
without any help from us.

09:23.198 --> 09:25.798
So with any luck,
they'll like what they see

09:25.868 --> 09:27.467
and we'll pass this inspection.

09:27.536 --> 09:28.970
BUG: What happens if we don't?

09:29.038 --> 09:30.703
BULLET: Then we don't get
to become Outlaws.

09:30.773 --> 09:32.673
BUG: Oh, so that's it, then?

09:32.740 --> 09:36.643
BULLET: Let's not try to find out, okay?

09:36.711 --> 09:37.945
BUG: Alright.

09:39.514 --> 09:41.081
(engines approaching)

09:41.149 --> 09:44.851
BULLET: Chef. Go let 'em in.

09:44.919 --> 09:49.856
♪

09:49.924 --> 09:54.793
♪

09:54.863 --> 09:59.565
♪

09:59.634 --> 10:03.003
♪

10:03.071 --> 10:05.538
THE DEVIL: What you all lookin at?

10:05.606 --> 10:07.706
Let's get this party started!

10:07.774 --> 10:09.741
BIKERS: Yeah!

10:09.811 --> 10:12.745
(bikers talking loudly)

10:12.813 --> 10:15.681
(bikers talking loudly)

10:15.750 --> 10:17.616
(Falco sighs)

10:22.551 --> 10:23.984
BULLET: We can add
more bunks if we need to,

10:24.052 --> 10:26.153
but right now we got space for eight.

10:26.221 --> 10:27.488
THE DEVIL:
Where's the sound you had that guy

10:27.556 --> 10:29.456
wire this place for?

10:29.524 --> 10:32.359
BULLET: Chef, you wanna
throw some tunes on?

10:34.929 --> 10:35.995
THE DEVIL: How about a beer?

10:36.063 --> 10:37.998
Or are you gonna let me die of thirst?

10:38.066 --> 10:41.500
♪

10:41.568 --> 10:44.336
♪

10:44.405 --> 10:47.106
THE DEVIL: So, I see a clubhouse.

10:47.176 --> 10:49.275
But I don't see a fourth guy.

10:49.344 --> 10:50.875
FALCO: In the corner right there.

10:50.945 --> 10:52.577
That's Darko.

10:52.647 --> 10:53.613
THE DEVIL: Darko!

10:53.682 --> 10:55.280
Over here!

10:55.350 --> 11:00.419
♪

11:00.488 --> 11:02.822
THE DEVIL: Where you from, new guy?

11:02.889 --> 11:04.856
DARKO: West.

11:04.926 --> 11:07.259
THE DEVIL: Another one
of your Left Coast refugees?

11:07.327 --> 11:10.562
BULLET: Yeah, we rode together
out in Bakersfield.

11:10.630 --> 11:12.264
THE DEVIL:
What brings you to Petersburg?

11:12.332 --> 11:13.465
DARKO: Work.

11:13.533 --> 11:15.000
THE DEVIL: Oh, yeah? What are you doing?

11:15.068 --> 11:17.369
DARKO: Lookin' for it.
Why, you got anything?

11:17.437 --> 11:19.904
THE DEVIL: Matter of fact, I do.

11:19.974 --> 11:22.106
You can go wash my bike.

11:23.409 --> 11:26.610
What's the matter? Too complicated?

11:26.679 --> 11:28.379
You want me to write it down?

11:28.448 --> 11:29.947
Can it even read?

11:30.015 --> 11:31.582
DARKO: Which one is it?

11:31.652 --> 11:33.585
THE DEVIL: The one with three wheels.

11:36.423 --> 11:38.322
THE DEVIL: You!

11:38.392 --> 11:41.058
The wannabe!

11:41.126 --> 11:42.125
BUG: Huh?

11:42.195 --> 11:44.062
THE DEVIL: You a California girl too?

11:44.129 --> 11:45.129
BUG: No, no.

11:45.197 --> 11:48.032
Uh, yeah, but I do know how to surf.

11:48.100 --> 11:49.267
(The Devil laughs)

11:49.336 --> 11:51.134
THE DEVIL: Now, where did you find him?

11:51.203 --> 11:53.904
BULLET: I caught him
trying to steal my bike.

11:56.107 --> 11:58.642
(The Devil laughs)

11:58.711 --> 12:00.878
THE DEVIL: Fair play, brother!

12:00.946 --> 12:03.013
Well, Mr. Bug...

12:03.081 --> 12:05.115
why don't you surf on outside

12:05.183 --> 12:07.451
and keep an eye on our bikes?

12:07.519 --> 12:08.586
BUG: Yeah.

12:12.124 --> 12:14.823
THE DEVIL: You got somewhere private?

12:14.894 --> 12:16.125
BULLET: Back there.

12:16.195 --> 12:18.195
THE DEVIL: Let's see it.

12:18.264 --> 12:22.599
♪

12:22.667 --> 12:25.269
♪

12:25.336 --> 12:27.537
SPUTNIK: Beers for fears.

12:27.605 --> 12:29.004
FALCO: What happened to the hair?

12:29.072 --> 12:32.542
SPUTNIK: Ah... crabs or some shit.

12:32.610 --> 12:37.212
♪

12:37.282 --> 12:39.548
♪

12:39.618 --> 12:41.865
SNIPER: So you rode with Darko.

12:44.288 --> 12:45.520
How'd you meet him?

12:45.588 --> 12:46.956
BULLET: Through Chef.

12:47.024 --> 12:49.292
We were both moving his product.

12:49.360 --> 12:50.558
SNIPER: Crystal, right?

12:50.628 --> 12:51.927
BULLET: Mostly.

12:51.995 --> 12:53.195
THE DEVIL: So you've got production

12:53.264 --> 12:55.197
and distribution skills?

12:55.265 --> 12:56.597
Good to know.

12:56.667 --> 12:59.034
SNIPER: Remind me
why you came here again.

12:59.102 --> 13:01.037
BULLET: I moved
with my Mongols chapter boss.

13:01.105 --> 13:04.004
He got shipped out with the navy.

13:04.073 --> 13:06.106
You know the rest.

13:06.176 --> 13:07.942
Anything else?

13:08.010 --> 13:10.446
THE DEVIL:
This old lady of yours, Meredith.

13:10.514 --> 13:12.815
She move here with you?

13:12.883 --> 13:15.895
BULLET: Crowbar mention her
in one of your Sunday talks?

13:17.386 --> 13:20.054
She's from around here.

13:20.123 --> 13:21.288
SNIPER: How'd you meet her?

13:21.357 --> 13:22.823
BULLET: She was a client.

13:22.892 --> 13:26.094
THE DEVIL: Yeah? You trim her topiary?

13:26.163 --> 13:27.428
(Bullet chuckles)

13:27.496 --> 13:31.099
THE DEVIL:
Looking forward to meeting her.

13:31.168 --> 13:33.969
So you want to be Outlaws,

13:34.037 --> 13:37.071
few things you need to understand.

13:37.139 --> 13:41.008
This is us, up near Richmond.

13:41.076 --> 13:44.177
This is you, Petersburg.

13:44.245 --> 13:48.215
This is the I-95,

13:48.283 --> 13:50.049
running north-south.

13:50.119 --> 13:54.321
This is the I-85 to Charlotte.

13:54.389 --> 13:57.390
And this is the 4-60 to the coast.

13:57.460 --> 14:02.562
If our fair state's a body,
then these are the veins.

14:02.630 --> 14:05.231
But here is the main line.

14:05.301 --> 14:09.970
It's got white lines running
all the way up from Florida.

14:11.038 --> 14:12.004
(snorts a line)

14:13.908 --> 14:16.009
If you follow me.

14:16.076 --> 14:19.513
But you know,
if this artery gets blocked,

14:19.581 --> 14:23.216
then the whole body falls apart.

14:25.620 --> 14:28.086
Our problem with the Maggots
'round here is makin'

14:28.155 --> 14:31.090
a lot of folks sick.

14:31.158 --> 14:33.926
You want to make it as Outlaws,

14:33.995 --> 14:35.293
you're gonna have to show me

14:35.363 --> 14:38.398
you can take care of the problem.

14:38.466 --> 14:42.466
♪

14:42.537 --> 14:45.538
♪

14:45.605 --> 14:46.938
(Bullet snorts a line)

14:49.043 --> 14:50.142
BULLET: Okay.

14:50.210 --> 14:52.411
So, we pass the inspection?

14:52.479 --> 14:56.181
'Cause if it's all the same to you,
I got plans with my old lady.

14:56.250 --> 14:58.129
SNIPER: Oh, we'll leave
when we're good and ready,

14:58.163 --> 14:59.211
hang-around.

15:01.831 --> 15:03.522
THE DEVIL: Grab us some beers, Chef!

15:03.590 --> 15:06.224
And some shots.

15:07.360 --> 15:08.559
BULLET: Looks like
we're gonna be here a while.

15:08.628 --> 15:09.927
FALCO: Seriously, man?
I have somewhere to go.

15:09.995 --> 15:10.995
BULLET: Listen, okay?

15:11.065 --> 15:12.230
The Devil's in a talkative mood,
alright?

15:12.298 --> 15:14.899
We're gonna have to stay here
as long as they want to hang around.

15:22.875 --> 15:25.341
(cell phone buzzing)

15:30.426 --> 15:32.326
MARTHA: What's up?

15:32.394 --> 15:34.528
SARAH JANE:
Looks like Charlie's running late.

15:34.596 --> 15:36.363
MARTHA: Well, not to worry.

15:36.432 --> 15:37.597
You wanna keep drawing?

15:37.667 --> 15:39.500
SARAH JANE: Can't concentrate today.

15:39.567 --> 15:42.536
MARTHA: Well, that's understandable.

15:42.605 --> 15:45.138
It's not gonna be the same
around here when you move.

15:45.206 --> 15:47.506
SARAH JANE: Well, I don't know.

15:47.575 --> 15:48.966
MARTHA: Don't know what?

15:50.611 --> 15:51.778
(Sarah Jane sighs)

15:51.846 --> 15:54.114
SARAH JANE: I don't know if I'm going.

15:57.318 --> 15:58.586
MARTHA: What do you mean?

16:00.254 --> 16:03.123
SARAH JANE: Situation's changed.

16:08.229 --> 16:09.629
CASEY: Big one.

16:09.697 --> 16:12.514
Nearly got away,
but I got him in the end.

16:14.648 --> 16:15.735
What?

16:18.272 --> 16:19.504
BUG: You seen this?

16:19.573 --> 16:22.140
Got my hands on one of
these new smart phones.

16:22.210 --> 16:24.043
DARKO: Where'd you get that?

16:25.346 --> 16:27.611
BUG: I got it at the mall.

16:27.681 --> 16:30.615
DARKO: Oh yeah,
were you getting your nails done?

16:30.683 --> 16:31.682
BUG: I'm telling you, man.

16:31.751 --> 16:34.576
Smart phones are changing the world.

16:36.523 --> 16:37.489
BULLET: What are you doing?

16:37.557 --> 16:38.789
BUG: Ah, check it out, man.

16:38.859 --> 16:40.827
This thing records video.

16:42.128 --> 16:44.428
DARKO: Not if you keep
recording me, it doesn't.

16:46.466 --> 16:48.232
Did you film me washing this trike?

16:50.169 --> 16:53.504
BUG: Uh... yeah?

16:57.110 --> 16:59.177
DARKO: Why don't you
record this instead?

17:03.448 --> 17:08.050
(urine trickling)

17:08.121 --> 17:11.521
♪

17:11.589 --> 17:13.691
♪

17:13.759 --> 17:19.997
(rock music playing)

17:20.065 --> 17:24.602
FALCO: Hey... Hey.

17:24.670 --> 17:27.403
Really? Do you have to do that?

17:27.471 --> 17:30.007
SPUTNIK: Yes.

17:30.075 --> 17:33.442
SNIPER: Chef, two beers.

17:33.511 --> 17:38.448
(rock music playing)

17:38.517 --> 17:43.251
(rock music playing)

17:43.505 --> 17:45.721
SNIPER: Hey, sit down.

17:54.915 --> 17:56.816
SNIPER: So...

17:56.884 --> 18:00.251
how's the tree business, hang-around?

18:00.320 --> 18:02.654
FALCO: Oh, you know...

18:02.722 --> 18:05.124
They grow and I cut 'em.

18:06.460 --> 18:08.661
SNIPER: There's something I
can't wrap my head around.

18:08.729 --> 18:13.231
How do you go from making
big bucks as a meth cook

18:13.300 --> 18:15.905
to yard work for nickels and dimes?

18:20.472 --> 18:22.973
FALCO: You know...

18:23.042 --> 18:25.309
I got messed up, man.

18:25.377 --> 18:26.952
I had to get out.

18:30.084 --> 18:31.750
SNIPER: So tell me about your job.

18:31.818 --> 18:33.451
Like yesterday...

18:33.519 --> 18:34.484
You cut any trees?

18:34.554 --> 18:35.353
FALCO: Uh-huh.

18:35.422 --> 18:36.854
SNIPER: Whereabouts?

18:36.923 --> 18:39.789
FALCO: Uh, farm just north of here.

18:39.858 --> 18:41.892
SNIPER: Where?

18:41.961 --> 18:45.363
FALCO: Amelia County.

18:45.432 --> 18:47.030
SNIPER: Where in Amelia?

18:47.099 --> 18:49.032
(Falco chuckles)

18:49.102 --> 18:51.335
FALCO: Are you serious?

18:51.403 --> 18:52.663
SNIPER: Very.

18:55.074 --> 18:57.441
FALCO: Just north of Mannboro.

18:57.509 --> 18:59.115
Took down a big elm.

19:01.346 --> 19:03.547
SNIPER: Help me out with something.

19:03.615 --> 19:07.718
What do they call that long two-man saw?

19:07.786 --> 19:10.621
FALCO: Um, I don't know.
I call it a long two-man saw.

19:10.689 --> 19:13.624
SPUTNIK: It's 'crosscut.'

19:13.692 --> 19:15.459
It's a crosscut saw.

19:16.729 --> 19:18.228
SNIPER: See?

19:18.297 --> 19:20.230
The commie knows.

19:20.298 --> 19:21.789
But you don't.

19:24.535 --> 19:26.361
FALCO: I just do the job, man.

19:28.673 --> 19:31.007
SNIPER: Don't see
any calluses on those hands.

19:31.076 --> 19:34.289
FALCO: I moisturize. You should try it.

19:36.513 --> 19:37.814
SNIPER: Why can't I get it
out of my head

19:37.883 --> 19:40.383
that you're full of shit?

19:40.451 --> 19:42.851
FALCO: Maybe 'cause
your head is full of shit.

19:48.393 --> 19:49.759
MARTHA: I thought
you were moving for art school,

19:49.826 --> 19:51.894
and now you're all about this boyfriend.

19:53.364 --> 19:54.497
(Casey kisses Martha)

19:54.565 --> 19:55.830
CASEY: Did you pick up the plastic wrap?

19:55.900 --> 19:57.398
MARTHA: Just use foil.

19:57.467 --> 19:59.334
CASEY: So fridge, not freezer?

19:59.403 --> 20:00.701
Looks like we're having rabbit tomorrow.

20:00.770 --> 20:02.003
MARTHA: Or I save one for tomorrow.

20:02.071 --> 20:03.971
I mean, if he's not coming.

20:04.040 --> 20:05.606
CASEY: What? Your friend's not coming?

20:05.675 --> 20:06.842
SARAH JANE: He's running late.

20:06.911 --> 20:07.910
MARTHA: I'm just saying,
at these prices,

20:07.978 --> 20:09.278
if he doesn't make it...

20:09.346 --> 20:11.578
CASEY: Hey, hey, hey!
If Sarah Jane says he's coming,

20:11.647 --> 20:13.980
I'm all for showing some faith, hm?

20:14.049 --> 20:15.916
♪

20:15.984 --> 20:18.787
(bottles clinking)

20:20.022 --> 20:20.922
FALCO: Hey, we're nearly out of beer.

20:20.990 --> 20:23.424
BULLET: We better get more.

20:27.931 --> 20:29.563
SARAH JANE: Hey. What's up?

20:29.632 --> 20:31.664
FALCO: Listen, I don't know if
I'm gonna be able to make it.

20:31.733 --> 20:33.767
SARAH JANE: Seriously?

20:39.953 --> 20:44.323
(metal music playing)

20:44.391 --> 20:47.526
(metal music playing)

20:47.595 --> 20:48.759
(Sputnik snorts a line)

20:49.663 --> 20:52.931
BUG: Pretty sure you don't
have to do that outside.

20:54.268 --> 20:57.301
Can I catch a ride off that?

20:57.371 --> 20:59.538
If I could just take a drag...

20:59.606 --> 21:02.973
(metal music playing)

21:03.042 --> 21:05.042
BUG: Party's inside. What are you...

21:05.112 --> 21:06.144
What are you doin' out here?

21:06.211 --> 21:07.979
SPUTNIK: I got business.

21:12.551 --> 21:15.286
(starts engine)

21:15.355 --> 21:16.954
(engine stalls)

21:19.057 --> 21:21.991
(engine sputtering)

21:23.128 --> 21:24.261
SPUTNIK: You've gotta be kidding me.

21:24.329 --> 21:26.130
FALCO: Hey, Bug?

21:26.199 --> 21:27.531
I need you to go buy beer.

21:27.599 --> 21:28.566
Take Bullet's truck.

21:28.634 --> 21:29.833
BUG: Me?

21:29.902 --> 21:30.933
FALCO: Yeah, yeah.

21:31.002 --> 21:32.435
Just buy as much as that gets,
okay, and be quick.

21:32.505 --> 21:33.836
BUG: Hey, where's the nearest store?

21:33.905 --> 21:34.570
FALCO: I don't know.

21:34.640 --> 21:36.239
SPUTNIK: I know a place.

21:36.307 --> 21:38.508
BUG: Like, uh, for beer?

21:41.881 --> 21:44.147
(truck engine starts)

21:44.215 --> 21:48.250
♪

21:48.319 --> 21:52.355
♪

21:52.423 --> 21:55.291
♪

21:55.359 --> 21:59.362
♪

21:59.431 --> 22:02.332
♪

22:02.401 --> 22:04.467
♪

22:04.536 --> 22:05.801
BUG: Do you have to do that, man?

22:05.869 --> 22:07.202
It's Bullet's truck.

22:07.270 --> 22:09.771
(phone ringing)

22:09.840 --> 22:13.275
SPUTNIK: (speaking Hungarian)

22:13.344 --> 22:18.980
(speaking Hungarian)

22:20.184 --> 22:22.550
BUG: Hey, man, can I ask you something?

22:22.619 --> 22:24.920
I heard you have to kill
someone to get patched.

22:24.988 --> 22:26.855
Is that, like, true?

22:26.923 --> 22:30.025
SPUTNIK: What's it to you, hm?

22:30.094 --> 22:31.359
BUG: Just making conversation, man.

22:31.429 --> 22:34.363
Trying to start a dialogue,
you and me, you know?

22:36.467 --> 22:39.201
(bikers cheering & yelling)

22:39.269 --> 22:42.403
(bikers cheering & yelling)

22:42.471 --> 22:45.539
(bikers cheering & yelling)

22:45.608 --> 22:46.974
THE DEVIL: Bullet!

22:47.044 --> 22:48.409
Still undefeated!

22:48.478 --> 22:51.546
And again, bank takes all!

22:51.615 --> 22:52.579
(laughing)

22:52.648 --> 22:55.450
Chef! Get over here!

22:55.518 --> 22:57.285
You're next!

22:57.354 --> 22:59.052
<i>FALCO: Eight hours in,
and The Devil's decided</i>

22:59.122 --> 23:00.988
<i>he wants entertainment.</i>

23:01.057 --> 23:02.457
<i>And we're it.</i>

23:02.525 --> 23:03.523
FALCO: What are you doing?

23:03.593 --> 23:05.925
SNIPER: Raising the stakes.

23:05.994 --> 23:10.397
♪

23:10.467 --> 23:12.467
THE DEVIL: You two better mean it.

23:12.535 --> 23:16.435
♪

23:16.505 --> 23:19.140
♪

23:19.208 --> 23:21.208
THE DEVIL: Three, two, one...

23:21.277 --> 23:22.476
Wrestle!

23:22.544 --> 23:26.313
BIKER: Yeah, yeah!
Come on, come on, come on!

23:26.382 --> 23:28.249
THE DEVIL: I said, like you mean it!

23:28.317 --> 23:32.419
(bikers cheering & yelling)

23:32.797 --> 23:34.288
THE DEVIL: Come on!

23:34.355 --> 23:39.358
(bikers cheering & yelling)

23:39.427 --> 23:40.894
THE DEVIL: Yeah!

23:40.961 --> 23:44.096
♪

23:44.165 --> 23:45.798
♪

23:45.866 --> 23:47.967
(Falco yells)

23:48.036 --> 23:51.304
(Falco breathing heavily)

23:51.372 --> 23:54.007
THE DEVIL: Still champion!

23:54.075 --> 23:57.176
Even if Chef did throw the fight.

24:01.817 --> 24:04.249
♪

24:04.318 --> 24:05.483
BUG: Aren't you coming?

24:05.553 --> 24:08.453
SPUTNIK: You go get beer. I wait here.

24:08.522 --> 24:09.855
BUG: Okay.

24:09.923 --> 24:14.759
♪

24:14.828 --> 24:18.530
♪

24:18.598 --> 24:22.034
♪

24:22.102 --> 24:23.035
(truck door closes)

24:23.103 --> 24:27.873
♪

24:27.942 --> 24:32.877
♪

24:32.947 --> 24:37.013
♪

24:37.083 --> 24:41.385
♪

24:41.454 --> 24:46.391
(rock music playing)

24:46.460 --> 24:51.395
(rock music playing)

24:51.464 --> 24:54.265
(rock music playing)

24:54.334 --> 24:56.933
(rock music playing)

24:57.002 --> 24:59.002
THE DEVIL: And one for yourself, Chef.

24:59.072 --> 25:00.471
FALCO: Nah, I'm good.

25:00.538 --> 25:02.906
THE DEVIL: Get yourself a beer.

25:02.976 --> 25:04.441
FALCO: Actually, this is the last one

25:04.509 --> 25:07.912
until Bug gets back with more.

25:07.980 --> 25:11.080
In the meantime, here. Help yourself.

25:11.817 --> 25:14.984
THE DEVIL: Turn that music off, now!

25:19.548 --> 25:22.749
Bullet, Darko! Over here!

25:30.491 --> 25:33.660
Maybe you two rode
together with the Mongols,

25:33.728 --> 25:37.529
but that don't mean you're
gonna cut it with the Outlaws.

25:37.598 --> 25:39.566
And I ain't saying it just because

25:39.634 --> 25:44.103
you ran out of freakin' beer!

25:44.172 --> 25:47.573
I'm saying it because this club...

25:47.641 --> 25:51.375
did not come to this town to party!

25:51.444 --> 25:55.480
We came here to do business.

25:55.548 --> 25:57.449
And your business...

25:57.617 --> 25:59.550
And your business...

25:59.619 --> 26:03.054
And all our business...

26:03.123 --> 26:06.656
is to step up and represent.

26:08.729 --> 26:11.561
That means when called upon,

26:11.631 --> 26:14.565
you fight for this club,

26:14.634 --> 26:17.401
you kill for this club,

26:17.470 --> 26:20.605
and you die for this club.

26:20.673 --> 26:25.375
And it also means,
that when called upon,

26:25.444 --> 26:28.346
you take a little burn on the hand...

26:28.413 --> 26:32.516
and you keep the clubhouse
fridge full of beer.

26:32.585 --> 26:36.220
Now...

26:36.288 --> 26:38.247
We're gonna wait.

26:40.259 --> 26:42.648
With the music off.

26:46.265 --> 26:49.133
Nice and quiet.

26:49.201 --> 26:52.301
And think about this...

26:52.371 --> 26:55.238
until the beer gets here.

27:02.180 --> 27:06.383
(slow rock music playing)

27:06.451 --> 27:08.416
CASEY: Should I set a fourth plate?

27:08.486 --> 27:10.051
Just in case?

27:10.121 --> 27:12.628
MARTHA: Are you sure it's the
right thing to get involved?

27:14.259 --> 27:16.759
SARAH JANE: We've gotten involved.

27:16.827 --> 27:18.493
That's just how it is.

27:18.561 --> 27:20.561
MARTHA: That's a bit fatalistic,
isn't it?

27:20.631 --> 27:23.165
I mean, after all the work
you did to get into Savannah.

27:23.233 --> 27:24.700
You don't have to give
it all up for him.

27:24.769 --> 27:26.335
CASEY: Ah, here.

27:26.403 --> 27:29.136
Nothing stops you from seeing each other

27:29.205 --> 27:31.071
on your vacations.

27:31.141 --> 27:32.273
Ah?

27:32.343 --> 27:34.643
SARAH JANE: Um, no thanks.

27:34.711 --> 27:35.844
MARTHA: No thanks?

27:35.913 --> 27:37.779
Since when have you ever
turned down a drink?

27:41.852 --> 27:43.240
MARTHA: Table.

27:45.721 --> 27:47.244
Sarah Jane?

27:51.795 --> 27:54.595
SARAH JANE: I'm eight weeks pregnant.

27:54.663 --> 27:56.596
MARTHA: Oh.

28:00.135 --> 28:01.669
SPUTNIK: Finally, man.
What is your problem?

28:01.738 --> 28:03.203
Come on, hurry up!

28:03.271 --> 28:06.105
BUG: I hope this is enough beer.

28:07.309 --> 28:11.010
♪

28:11.079 --> 28:12.112
BUG: What's the problem?

28:12.181 --> 28:14.448
SPUTNIK: Don't be so obvious.

28:14.516 --> 28:17.017
Come on, let's go.

28:19.621 --> 28:20.686
BUG: What is it, what is it?

28:20.756 --> 28:22.088
SPUTNIK: Just finish up and let's go.

28:22.157 --> 28:24.023
BUG: What's going on?

28:24.093 --> 28:26.026
SPUTNIK: Come on.

28:26.095 --> 28:27.294
Go!

28:28.463 --> 28:30.396
(car engine starts)

28:30.465 --> 28:34.334
♪

28:34.403 --> 28:37.237
♪

28:45.046 --> 28:47.779
(rock music playing)

28:47.847 --> 28:50.682
BUG: Chef, Chef...

28:50.751 --> 28:51.670
FALCO: What?

28:51.670 --> 28:53.719
BUG: We saw something out there.

28:53.788 --> 28:54.920
FALCO: What was it?

28:54.989 --> 28:56.822
BUG: I'm pretty sure
we were being followed.

28:56.891 --> 28:57.784
FALCO: By who?

28:57.784 --> 28:58.758
BUG: I dunno, it was, like, a black car.

28:58.826 --> 29:00.092
Sputnik saw it too.

29:00.161 --> 29:02.059
THE DEVIL: You wanna be boss
of a successful chapter,

29:02.128 --> 29:04.896
you gotta know how to get
the best outta your boys.

29:04.964 --> 29:07.464
It's like being a baseball manager.

29:07.534 --> 29:10.001
You take a random bunch of guys,

29:10.069 --> 29:13.005
and it's your job to
turn them into a team.

29:16.796 --> 29:18.930
Take Foghorn here.

29:18.999 --> 29:22.700
He ain't gonna win any
awards for public speaking,

29:22.769 --> 29:25.102
but when I use him to send a message,

29:25.171 --> 29:28.873
it comes through loud and clear!

29:28.942 --> 29:32.943
You gotta deploy your guys
according to their talents.

29:33.012 --> 29:37.948
Just like baseball,
you gotta have pitching and defense.

29:38.017 --> 29:39.615
But you wanna be winners,

29:39.684 --> 29:42.219
you gotta have guys
who can score you runs.

29:42.288 --> 29:45.588
Solid hitters and sluggers.

29:45.657 --> 29:46.656
Where's your guy Bug?

29:46.724 --> 29:48.759
Bug! Come here.

29:48.826 --> 29:50.693
BUG: Yeah, I, I was just telling Chef...

29:50.762 --> 29:52.695
THE DEVIL: Yeah, shh! Sit down.

29:54.833 --> 29:57.667
BUG: Hey, what are you doing?

29:57.736 --> 29:59.001
THE DEVIL: Hold nice and still.

29:59.070 --> 30:00.269
BUG: Yeah...

30:02.240 --> 30:03.707
THE DEVIL: Like I was saying...

30:03.776 --> 30:06.276
you need different kinds of hitters.

30:06.344 --> 30:08.211
Take Ted Williams.

30:08.279 --> 30:10.980
The Thumper was all about precision.

30:11.048 --> 30:16.786
Hit his share of taters,
but more often than not...

30:16.854 --> 30:20.021
he'd step up to the plate,

30:20.092 --> 30:24.926
and he would lay one
perfectly into a gap.

30:27.230 --> 30:30.031
(The Devil laughing)

30:30.101 --> 30:32.867
THE DEVIL: Yeah! (laughing)

30:32.936 --> 30:34.236
Again, ashtray!

30:34.305 --> 30:38.740
♪

30:38.809 --> 30:41.609
♪

30:41.677 --> 30:44.945
(voices in other room)

30:45.015 --> 30:49.718
♪

30:49.786 --> 30:50.852
♪

30:50.921 --> 30:52.787
THE DEVIL: Like I was saying...

30:52.855 --> 30:54.855
different types of hitters.

30:54.924 --> 30:57.092
Precision guys like Williams,

30:57.161 --> 31:00.662
and your out-and-out
sluggers like Babe Ruth.

31:00.730 --> 31:03.097
Now, the Bambino didn't
walk to the plate thinkin',

31:03.165 --> 31:07.102
"Heck, I'd love to hit me a single."

31:07.170 --> 31:11.972
He'd just close his eyes
and swing for the fences.

31:12.875 --> 31:14.608
CASEY: Oh, damn!

31:14.676 --> 31:15.875
I...

31:15.944 --> 31:18.311
Look, it's a question of responsibility.

31:18.381 --> 31:21.174
MARTHA: Casey, don't hand-talk
with wine in front of you.

31:21.210 --> 31:22.778
CASEY: I'm making a point.

31:24.653 --> 31:25.786
Listen, I'm not one to judge,

31:25.855 --> 31:27.622
but what will your church friends say

31:27.690 --> 31:30.824
when they find out?

31:30.893 --> 31:36.029
SARAH JANE: Well...
maybe they won't judge either.

31:36.097 --> 31:37.998
I didn't mean it to happen, Casey.

31:38.067 --> 31:39.900
CASEY: No, what you mean
is you did what you wanted,

31:39.969 --> 31:43.336
but you hoped it wouldn't happen.

31:43.404 --> 31:45.638
SARAH JANE: You know what?

31:45.708 --> 31:49.909
I think I'm gonna have that
glass of wine after all.

31:51.380 --> 31:54.047
(sighs)

31:54.115 --> 31:56.048
Mmm...

31:56.116 --> 31:57.217
That's good.

31:57.286 --> 31:59.318
♪

31:59.778 --> 32:00.710
FALCO: Hey.

32:00.778 --> 32:02.679
Saw a black car outside, right?

32:02.747 --> 32:04.065
- Yes?
- BUG: Yes.

32:04.065 --> 32:06.449
FALCO: Hold down the fort.
I'm gonna check it out.

32:06.517 --> 32:11.118
(bikers cheering & yelling)

32:11.188 --> 32:12.653
(bikers cheering & yelling)

32:12.721 --> 32:14.355
BIKER: Yeah, let's see somethin'!

32:14.423 --> 32:17.291
(bikers cheering & yelling)

32:17.359 --> 32:22.297
(bikers cheering & yelling)

32:22.365 --> 32:23.464
(bikers cheering & yelling)

32:23.532 --> 32:28.469
♪

32:28.537 --> 32:31.137
♪

32:31.207 --> 32:35.710
♪

32:35.778 --> 32:37.612
(car engine starts)

32:37.680 --> 32:42.348
♪

32:42.417 --> 32:47.019
♪

32:47.088 --> 32:48.688
♪

32:48.757 --> 32:54.094
(bikers cheering & yelling)

32:54.163 --> 32:58.240
(bikers cheering & yelling)

32:58.240 --> 33:00.066
SNIPER: That hurt, old man?

33:00.134 --> 33:00.840
I tell you what,

33:00.840 --> 33:03.737
if you can't do your old lady,
I'll take of her for ya!

33:03.805 --> 33:07.981
(bikers cheering & yelling)

33:07.981 --> 33:10.308
THE DEVIL:
Looks like we've found a weakness!

33:10.377 --> 33:14.579
(bikers cheering & yelling)

33:14.650 --> 33:15.580
BIKER: Bullet, come on!

33:15.651 --> 33:16.648
Come on, man!

33:16.717 --> 33:21.053
♪

33:21.122 --> 33:26.057
♪

33:26.126 --> 33:30.429
♪

33:36.226 --> 33:39.626
THE DEVIL: Looks like you
overstepped the mark, Bullet.

33:41.497 --> 33:43.462
CROWD: Yeah!

33:43.532 --> 33:45.298
THE DEVIL: Or maybe
you just stepped up to it.

33:45.366 --> 33:47.433
BIKER: Yeah!

33:47.502 --> 33:50.302
THE DEVIL: That which don't
kill us only makes us stronger.

33:50.372 --> 33:51.371
Right, Bullet?

33:51.440 --> 33:52.806
CROWD: Yeah!

33:52.875 --> 33:54.441
BULLET: I'm too old for this shit.

33:54.509 --> 33:56.276
THE DEVIL: I say it keeps a man young!

33:56.345 --> 33:57.743
CROWD: Yeah!

33:59.748 --> 34:01.548
FALCO: I saw a black car
outside with tinted windows.

34:01.615 --> 34:02.781
Is Meredith around?

34:02.851 --> 34:04.284
BULLET: (breathing heavily)
I don't know.

34:04.353 --> 34:06.786
I didn't call her.

34:06.855 --> 34:08.688
THE DEVIL: I wanna see more fighting.

34:08.757 --> 34:10.393
Darko...

34:13.527 --> 34:15.695
Chef!

34:15.764 --> 34:17.362
You and Darko!

34:17.431 --> 34:20.231
(crowd exclaiming)

34:26.139 --> 34:30.576
♪

34:30.643 --> 34:32.378
THE DEVIL: You boys got something
between you two,

34:32.447 --> 34:35.146
I can tell.

34:35.215 --> 34:39.217
How 'bout you work it out in the ring?

34:39.286 --> 34:42.753
You wanna be Outlaws?

34:42.822 --> 34:44.822
Fight like you mean it.

34:44.891 --> 34:46.692
(bikers cheering)

34:46.760 --> 34:48.358
BULLET: I need you on the door, okay?

34:48.427 --> 34:51.096
If you see anything at all,
you come tell me.

34:51.164 --> 34:53.231
THE DEVIL: As for rules,
there ain't any,

34:53.300 --> 34:55.634
so don't hold back on our account.

34:55.702 --> 34:57.135
You ready?

34:57.204 --> 34:59.036
Three, two...

34:59.106 --> 35:03.673
♪

35:03.742 --> 35:08.679
♪

35:08.748 --> 35:11.215
♪

35:11.284 --> 35:13.050
(bikers cheering & yelling)

35:13.119 --> 35:17.621
(bikers cheering & yelling)

35:17.690 --> 35:19.724
(crashing)

35:19.791 --> 35:23.728
(bikers cheering & yelling)

35:23.795 --> 35:25.663
(The Devil laughing)

35:27.199 --> 35:29.465
CASEY: Look, this is all just...

35:29.534 --> 35:32.235
It's... well, it's a surprise.

35:32.304 --> 35:35.704
Especially given the way
things ended with Donny.

35:35.773 --> 35:37.507
Martha and I were there for you then.

35:37.576 --> 35:39.208
And we're here for you now.

35:39.277 --> 35:41.344
You know that, right?

35:41.413 --> 35:42.545
We just don't want to see you end up...

35:42.614 --> 35:45.481
MARTHA: Who wants dessert?

35:45.550 --> 35:48.385
SARAH JANE: You know,
I don't think I have room for any more.

35:48.454 --> 35:49.585
But thanks.

35:49.655 --> 35:51.288
MARTHA: Oh, okay. You want some coffee?

35:51.356 --> 35:54.724
SARAH JANE: No,
I'm gonna go to Charlie's.

35:54.793 --> 35:56.291
CASEY: Sarah Jane, come on.

35:56.360 --> 35:58.427
The man stands you up
right when you need him...

35:58.496 --> 36:01.396
SARAH JANE: Yeah,
and I'm sure there's a good reason!

36:01.465 --> 36:04.500
I just want to make sure he's okay.

36:04.568 --> 36:08.771
But thanks for... all your support.

36:11.775 --> 36:16.711
(bikers cheering & yelling)

36:16.780 --> 36:21.717
(bikers cheering & yelling)

36:21.786 --> 36:26.722
(bikers cheering & yelling)

36:26.791 --> 36:31.726
(bikers cheering & yelling)

36:31.795 --> 36:33.728
(bikers cheering & yelling)

36:33.797 --> 36:38.733
♪

36:41.137 --> 36:46.074
(motorcycles revving)

36:46.141 --> 36:48.577
(motorcycles revving)

36:49.646 --> 36:53.648
♪

36:53.717 --> 36:58.518
♪

36:58.588 --> 37:02.590
♪

37:02.657 --> 37:06.460
♪

37:06.528 --> 37:11.231
♪

37:11.300 --> 37:15.135
♪

37:15.204 --> 37:16.670
♪

37:16.739 --> 37:19.773
(bikers cheering & yelling)

37:19.842 --> 37:21.041
BUG: There's a bunch of guys
out at the front.

37:21.110 --> 37:22.141
BULLET: What?

37:24.614 --> 37:26.213
BULLET: That's enough!

37:26.282 --> 37:27.780
I said, that's enough!

37:27.849 --> 37:29.349
THE DEVIL: I'll say when it's enough!

37:29.418 --> 37:32.052
BULLET: There's Maggots outside!

37:32.121 --> 37:35.288
THE DEVIL: Lock n' load, boys!

37:35.356 --> 37:39.592
♪

37:39.661 --> 37:44.164
♪

37:44.233 --> 37:48.233
♪

37:48.302 --> 37:51.836
♪

37:51.905 --> 37:57.175
♪

37:57.518 --> 37:59.210
DARKO: Pick one.

37:59.280 --> 38:04.215
♪

38:04.284 --> 38:08.719
♪

38:08.789 --> 38:13.192
♪

38:13.260 --> 38:15.693
♪

38:16.163 --> 38:18.896
THE DEVIL:
What are you gonna do about this?

38:18.965 --> 38:21.800
You boys gonna step up?

38:21.867 --> 38:24.168
'Cause this would be a good time.

38:24.237 --> 38:28.773
♪

38:30.344 --> 38:32.335
You gonna do this?

38:32.336 --> 38:35.403
Or do you want me to settle
it the old-fashioned way?

38:35.472 --> 38:40.409
♪

38:40.478 --> 38:43.445
♪

38:43.514 --> 38:46.181
♪

38:46.250 --> 38:47.817
BULLET: Let's go.

38:47.885 --> 38:50.452
♪

38:50.521 --> 38:53.255
♪

38:53.324 --> 38:54.822
FALCO: Coming?

38:56.559 --> 39:01.096
♪

39:01.164 --> 39:05.367
♪

39:05.436 --> 39:08.802
RAZOR: So, the ex-Mongol's
got a clubhouse.

39:08.871 --> 39:10.838
You with The Devil now?

39:10.907 --> 39:12.306
BULLET: Depends.

39:12.375 --> 39:14.509
We haven't decided if he deserves us.

39:14.577 --> 39:16.945
RAZOR: Well,
you better think hard about it.

39:17.014 --> 39:19.780
'Cause if this turns into
an Outlaws clubhouse,

39:19.849 --> 39:23.983
we'll burn it to the ground,
with or without anyone home.

39:24.054 --> 39:27.065
And if we see you riding
around here in Outlaws colours

39:27.670 --> 39:31.123
you're as good as dead.

39:31.193 --> 39:33.293
Let's go.

39:34.329 --> 39:37.164
(engines starting)

39:44.940 --> 39:50.043
(engines fading away)

39:50.110 --> 39:52.244
THE DEVIL: What'd you say?

39:52.313 --> 39:54.047
BULLET: Asked 'em to leave.

39:54.114 --> 39:56.382
It's time you guys left too.

39:56.451 --> 40:00.186
Party's over.

40:03.190 --> 40:08.193
♪

40:08.262 --> 40:11.197
THE DEVIL: Alright! Everyone, listen up!

40:11.264 --> 40:13.831
We just seen the problem
we got with Maggots

40:13.900 --> 40:17.503
trying to move in on
territory around here.

40:17.572 --> 40:19.471
Seems to me, we ain't got no choice

40:19.539 --> 40:23.141
but to send a message straight back.

40:23.210 --> 40:25.476
That's why I'm making you boys

40:25.545 --> 40:28.313
our new probate Chapter of Outlaws!

40:28.380 --> 40:30.347
(bikers cheering)

40:30.416 --> 40:31.983
THE DEVIL: Yeah!

40:32.052 --> 40:34.853
(laughing)

40:34.922 --> 40:37.521
(bikers cheering)

40:37.590 --> 40:41.492
THE DEVIL: Now, then!
Let's all have us some beers!

40:41.561 --> 40:45.295
(bikers cheering & laughing)

40:45.364 --> 40:49.065
♪

40:49.135 --> 40:50.335
♪

40:50.402 --> 40:53.436
(engines starting)

40:53.505 --> 40:55.072
THE DEVIL: Remember...

40:55.141 --> 40:57.541
this is just the start!

40:57.610 --> 40:59.309
You want all the way in,

40:59.378 --> 41:02.579
you got a lot left to prove, probate!

41:09.387 --> 41:11.920
(engines fading away)

41:11.989 --> 41:12.936
BUG: So who won?

41:12.936 --> 41:13.958
FALCO: Won what?

41:13.958 --> 41:14.713
BUG: Your fight.

41:14.713 --> 41:16.025
FALCO & DARKO: <i>I</i> did.

41:17.262 --> 41:20.563
(engines in distance)

41:20.632 --> 41:23.534
(engines in distance)

41:23.601 --> 41:26.369
FALCO: This is like putting
a target on our backs, right?

41:26.436 --> 41:27.436
BULLET: It's the price of admission

41:27.505 --> 41:30.472
if we wanna work undercover.

41:31.543 --> 41:33.342
FALCO: So what was The
Devil shooting his mouth off

41:33.411 --> 41:34.911
about earlier?

41:34.980 --> 41:36.244
BULLET: We'll see.

41:36.313 --> 41:39.181
He's definitely mixed
up in something big.

41:40.152 --> 41:43.219
BUG: Am I the only one here
who feels like a drink?

41:43.288 --> 41:45.153
DARKO: Amen to that, brother.

41:45.222 --> 41:47.389
BUG: Thank you.

41:47.458 --> 41:48.891
BULLET: Lock up when you're done.

41:48.958 --> 41:51.594
(Falco's engine starts)

41:51.663 --> 41:57.199
♪

41:57.268 --> 41:58.967
(Bullet sighs)

42:04.407 --> 42:07.842
<i>FALCO: Vagos, Mongols,</i>

42:07.911 --> 42:10.079
<i>and now the Outlaws...</i>

42:10.146 --> 42:12.914
<i>the further I travel from the real me,</i>

42:12.983 --> 42:16.150
<i>the harder it gets to find my way back.</i>

42:16.219 --> 42:18.820
♪

42:18.887 --> 42:22.489
♪

42:22.559 --> 42:24.092
(Falco sighs)

42:24.159 --> 42:26.360
FALCO: Hey, hey... I'm sorry.
I'm so sorry.

42:26.429 --> 42:27.829
SARAH JANE: It's okay. Here...

42:30.099 --> 42:31.599
What happened?

42:31.666 --> 42:36.603
♪

42:36.672 --> 42:40.440
♪

42:40.509 --> 42:42.242
SNIPER: Hey.

42:42.311 --> 42:44.010
You have a tree taken down lately?

42:44.079 --> 42:46.047
Like an Elm?

42:46.115 --> 42:47.215
FARMER: No...?

42:47.282 --> 42:49.550
SNIPER: Anyone else you know of?

42:49.619 --> 42:51.418
FARMER: No.

42:51.487 --> 42:52.885
(Sniper starts engine)

42:52.954 --> 42:54.588
SNIPER: Have a good one.

42:54.657 --> 42:58.492
♪

43:24.938 --> 43:27.338
<font color=#FF0000>- synced and corrected by sot26 -
www.addic7ed.com</font>

43:31.733 --> 43:32.733
_

43:32.733 --> 43:34.233
THE DEVIL: Your old lady, Chef?

43:34.302 --> 43:35.121
FALCO: Yes, she is.

43:35.121 --> 43:37.802
THE DEVIL: Then we're looking
forward to seeing her at the wedding.

43:37.871 --> 43:38.652
FALCO: What wedding?

43:38.652 --> 43:39.972
BULLET: This isn't just any wedding,

43:40.041 --> 43:41.440
it's hosted by a guy named Gator.

43:41.507 --> 43:43.407
Outlaws international president.

43:43.476 --> 43:45.309
SARAH JANE:
What are you so worried about?

43:45.378 --> 43:47.550
FALCO: Just don't want you
getting caught up in this.

43:47.550 --> 43:48.382
THE DEVIL: Come with me.

43:48.382 --> 43:50.215
COZT: You do ask a lot of questions.

43:50.284 --> 43:51.983
BULLET: Gator's got
his own trucking business?

43:52.052 --> 43:53.385
THE DEVIL: Among other things.

43:53.454 --> 43:55.387
GATOR: Yeah well it was
my truck that got jacked.

43:55.456 --> 43:57.088
And it happened on your turf.

43:57.157 --> 43:58.590
GATOR: There's a piece of
business the club needs

43:58.659 --> 44:00.125
you to take care of.

